	(302, 298, 'Monthly Report - Partners', '', 'monthly_report', 1, 'n', '', 'null', 'MONTHLY_REPORT_MITRA', '"<p><span style=\\"font-size:14px;\\"><strong>Guidance Note for completing monthly report (Implementing Partners):<\\/strong><\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><strong>Activity Completed<\\/strong><br \\/>\\nWe just want a quick update on (i) key activities \\/ events completed during the month; (ii) any significant issues arising and \\/ or changes in context; and (iii) key upcoming activities \\/ events over the next 3 months that the AIPJ2 team, DFAT and \\/ or Bappenas should be aware of (e.g. if they wish or need to attend).\\u00a0<br \\/><br \\/>\\nThe report should be completed by the designated Activity Manager within the implementing partners organisation, based on the information being collected through routine internal monitoring \\/ reporting. \\u00a0As necessary, the report should be \\u2018approved\\u2019 by a more senior agency official before being sent to AIPJ2.\\u00a0<br \\/><br \\/>\\nThe monthly report should be completed, at the very latest, by the 5th of each month (in the month following the reporting period), and submitted to designated AIPJ2 pillar Activity Manager). \\u00a0These reports will then be used to inform the AIPJ2 management team, DFAT and Bappenas of what is happening, including through the preparation of the overall AIPJ2 monthly dashboard reports.\\u00a0<br \\/><br \\/>\\nPlease provide key data with respect to number of people and \\/ or organisations involved, including the number of men, women and (if applicable) people with disabilities.<br \\/>\\n\\u00a0\\u00a0<br \\/>\\nTo record all other \\u00a0documentation that support that activities, use support document function to upload it.\\u00a0<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Changes In Context<\\/strong><br \\/>\\nThis section of the report should highlight any significant issues or problems encountered that have caused changes in the planned work \\/ activities. \\u00a0Changes in \\u2018context\\u2019 refers to such things as:<\\/p>\\n\\n<ul><li>Changes in government policy \\/ regulations, institutional structure, staffing or funding that is impacting (positively or negatively) on the work of the project\\u00a0<\\/li>\\n\\t<li>Changes in CSO leadership, priorities, staffing, funding etc that is impacting (positively or negatively) on the work of the project<\\/li>\\n\\t<li>Political changes \\u2013 at national or local levels \\u2013 that are impacting (positively or negatively) on the work of the project.\\u00a0<br \\/>\\n\\t\\u00a0<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>"', '"<p><span style=\\"font-size:14px;\\"><strong>Guidance Note for completing monthly report (Implementing Partners):<\\/strong><\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><strong>Activity Completed<\\/strong><br \\/>\\nWe just want a quick update on (i) key activities \\/ events completed during the month; (ii) any significant issues arising and \\/ or changes in context; and (iii) key upcoming activities \\/ events over the next 3 months that the AIPJ2 team, DFAT and \\/ or Bappenas should be aware of (e.g. if they wish or need to attend).\\u00a0<br \\/><br \\/>\\nThe report should be completed by the designated Activity Manager within the implementing partners organisation, based on the information being collected through routine internal monitoring \\/ reporting. \\u00a0As necessary, the report should be \\u2018approved\\u2019 by a more senior agency official before being sent to AIPJ2.\\u00a0<br \\/><br \\/>\\nThe monthly report should be completed, at the very latest, by the 5th of each month (in the month following the reporting period), and submitted to designated AIPJ2 pillar Activity Manager). \\u00a0These reports will then be used to inform the AIPJ2 management team, DFAT and Bappenas of what is happening, including through the preparation of the overall AIPJ2 monthly dashboard reports.\\u00a0<br \\/><br \\/>\\nPlease provide key data with respect to number of people and \\/ or organisations involved, including the number of men, women and (if applicable) people with disabilities.<br \\/>\\n\\u00a0\\u00a0<br \\/>\\nTo record all other \\u00a0documentation that support that activities, use support document function to upload it.\\u00a0<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Changes In Context<\\/strong><br \\/>\\nThis section of the report should highlight any significant issues or problems encountered that have caused changes in the planned work \\/ activities. \\u00a0Changes in \\u2018context\\u2019 refers to such things as:<\\/p>\\n\\n<ul><li>Changes in government policy \\/ regulations, institutional structure, staffing or funding that is impacting (positively or negatively) on the work of the project\\u00a0<\\/li>\\n\\t<li>Changes in CSO leadership, priorities, staffing, funding etc that is impacting (positively or negatively) on the work of the project<\\/li>\\n\\t<li>Political changes \\u2013 at national or local levels \\u2013 that are impacting (positively or negatively) on the work of the project.\\u00a0<br \\/>\\n\\t\\u00a0<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>"', '2018-05-03 14:21:21', 'Monthly Report - Partners', 1, '2018-08-23 22:15:28'),
