	(305, 298, 'Quarterly Report - Partner', '', 'quarterly_report', 44, 'n', '', '{"Progress towards achieving intermediate outcomes ":"<p>10.1 \\u00a0To what extent, and in relation to which policy and \\/ or implementation planning issues, do GOI and CSO partners have enhanced knowledge of: (i) underlying problems; and (ii) how to solve such problems based on evidence? \\u00a0<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>10.2 \\u00a0To what extent, and in what ways, are GOI and CSO partners working more effectively together to develop improved policy and support its implementation?<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>10.3 \\u00a0To what extent, and in what ways, do partners have enhanced institutional capacity (systems and skills) to support improved policy development \\u00a0and\\/or implementation?<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>10.4 \\u00a0To what extent, and in what ways, do GOI and CSO partners have enhanced understanding of how to promote and protect the rights of women and PWDs?<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><br \\/>\\nOther?<br \\/>\\n\\u00a0<\\/p>\\n"}', 'QUARTERLY-REPORTING', '"<p style=\\"margin:0cm 0cm 6pt;\\"><strong><span style=\\"font-size:14px;\\">Guidance Note for completing quarterly report (Indonesian Implementing Partners):<\\/span><\\/strong><\\/p>\\n\\n<p style=\\"margin:0cm 0cm 6pt;\\">Quarterly reports should focus on describing any progress made towards supporting AIPJ2 outcomes, and providing relevant evidence. \\u00a0The reports should also reflect on lessons learned and implications for forward planning.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p style=\\"margin:0cm 0cm 6pt;\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\n\\n<p style=\\"margin:0cm 0cm 6pt;\\"><strong>Leassons learned and \\/ or action required to streng then project effectiveness in the future <\\/strong>should summarise any changes in Activity strategy or scope that you think are required based on analysis of progress made, results being achieved (or not), and changes in context (lessons learned).<br \\/><br \\/><strong>Issues requiring further discussion and \\/ or coordination with AIPJ2<\\/strong> is to inform the follow up discussion \\u00a0and coordination requirements with AIPJ2.<br \\/><br \\/><span style=\\"font-size:12px;\\"><strong>Progress Towards Achieving Intermediate Outcomes <\\/strong>is structured around AIPJ2\\u2019s 4 key monitoring questions (Knowledge, Partnerships, Systems and Skills, GEDSI). If any of these are not relevant to your project \\/ activity during the reporting period, delete the sub-heading or just leave blank. As noted further below, please provide relevant summary data \\/ evidence, either here or as an attachment.<br \\/><br \\/><strong>Progress Towards Achieving End Of Facility Outcomes<\\/strong> should complement and synthesise, not simply repeat, what has been noted in monthly reports. It should highlight significant changes in context (the operating environment \\/ political economy) that are impacting, or may impact, on activity implementation. This might include shifts \\/ changes in government policy or priorities, re-structuring of partner agencies or changes in senior staff \\/ counterparts, ability of partners to co-fund activities, changes within the GOA team or context, etc). These changes in context may pose risks or offer up new opportunities.<\\/span><br \\/>\\n\\u00a0<\\/p>\\n\\n<p style=\\"margin:0cm 0cm 6pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size:12px;\\">The report should be completed by the designated Activity Manager within the implementing partner organisation, based on the information being collected through routine internal monitoring \\/ reporting. and the monthly reports. \\u00a0As necessary, the report should be \\u2018approved\\u2019 by a more senior agency official before being sent to AIPJ2. \\u00a0<br \\/>\\nThe quarterly report should be completed, at the very latest, by the 5th of April, July, October, and January each year and submitted to designated AIPJ2 pillar Activity Manager.\\u00a0<br \\/><br \\/>\\nPlease attach relevant data \\/ evidence sources, as appropriate, with respect to:<\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<ol>