	(1, '5.1.  In selecting investments the Partnership uses the following criteria:\r\n\r\n5.1.1.  Ability to demonstrate a clear and substantive contribution to one or more of the Partnership objectives;\r\n\r\n5.1.2.  ODA eligible as defined by the OECD Development Assistance Committee Reporting Directives on Overseas Development Assistance[1];\r\n\r\n5.1.3.  Plan for sustainability, in particular for activities aiming to contribute change in public service policy and practice;\r\n\r\n5.1.4.  If a direct service delivery initiative, need to demonstrate the purpose and likely impact of catalytic change;\r\n\r\n5.1.5.  Value for money;\r\n\r\n5.1.6.  Demonstrated transparency and accountability reforms included in the design of activities;\r\n\r\n5.1.7.  Demonstration of gender and disability sensitive reform and gender mainstreaming considerations across activity initiatives;\r\n\r\n5.1.8.  The time horizon for achieving progress is reasonable and plausible and there are adequate resources to support this;\r\n\r\n5.1.9.  Alignment with the strategic direction of Australia Development Cooperation with Indonesia and related Performance Assessment Frameworks;\r\n\r\n5.1.10.        Alignment with Indonesian and Australian government policy, in particular in relation to security cooperation, gender and economic diplomacy; and\r\n\r\n5.1.11.        Risk for either partner in undertaking the initiative can be managed to a satisfactory level.', 0, 15, NULL, 1, '2019-03-29 22:46:23');
